The paper focuses on developing a security monitoring framework for distributed computing infrastructures in the field of High Energy Physics (HEP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses virtualization and its impact on performance, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of Machine Learning algorithms for detecting malicious Jobs, which could place it in the categories of cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper collects and analyzes data related to resource consumption and system calls, which could also make it relevant to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
